<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="371" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,634,153,215]" box="[151,314,189,215]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,233,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1938,1963]" captionTargetBox="[236,1352,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1362,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. a–d. S.yingjiangica Cao &amp; Zhang, 2014; e–h. S. shiqianensis Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3933628/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
e–h, 3)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,261,1044]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,261,288]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Description.</emphasis>
Alcohol preserved specimens with body yellow, apical patch on vertex small, eyes pale gray, basal triangles on mesonotum indistinct (
<figureCitation box="[552,676,297,324]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1938,1963]" captionTargetBox="[236,1352,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1362,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. a–d. S.yingjiangica Cao &amp; Zhang, 2014; e–h. S. shiqianensis Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3933628/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Figs. 1e, g</figureCitation>
). Frontoclypeal area and anteclypeus broad, lorum small (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1422,297,324]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1938,1963]" captionTargetBox="[236,1352,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1362,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. a–d. S.yingjiangica Cao &amp; Zhang, 2014; e–h. S. shiqianensis Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3933628/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Fig. 1h</figureCitation>
). Fore wing and hind wing yellow, transparent (
<figureCitation box="[668,784,333,360]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1938,1963]" captionTargetBox="[236,1352,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1362,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. a–d. S.yingjiangica Cao &amp; Zhang, 2014; e–h. S. shiqianensis Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3933628/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Figs. 1e, f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,261,1044]" box="[199,1206,369,396]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">
Abdominal apodemes small, only extending to posterior margin of third sternite (
<figureCitation box="[1109,1193,369,396]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1858,1883]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,191,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,181,1839]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. S. shiqianensis Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. 2S abdominal apodemes; c. connective; d,i. anal tube appendage; e. apex of style, lateral view; f. style, dorsal view; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3933632/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,261,1044]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">
Pygofer side short, hind margin truncate, with microsetae at dorso-caudal angle (
<figureCitation box="[1100,1182,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1858,1883]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,191,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,181,1839]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. S. shiqianensis Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. 2S abdominal apodemes; c. connective; d,i. anal tube appendage; e. apex of style, lateral view; f. style, dorsal view; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3933632/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
). Anal tube appendage short and broad, with tooth at apex (
<figureCitation box="[562,683,441,468]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1858,1883]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,191,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,181,1839]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. S. shiqianensis Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. 2S abdominal apodemes; c. connective; d,i. anal tube appendage; e. apex of style, lateral view; f. style, dorsal view; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3933632/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Figs. 3a, d</figureCitation>
), or basal part broad, gradually narrowing apically, with the apical tooth directed ventrad (
<figureCitation box="[416,493,477,504]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1858,1883]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,191,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,181,1839]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. S. shiqianensis Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. 2S abdominal apodemes; c. connective; d,i. anal tube appendage; e. apex of style, lateral view; f. style, dorsal view; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3933632/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Fig. 3i</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate with irregular row of microsetae along dorsal outer margin from near base to subapex, with 4–5 macrosetae medially (
<figureCitation box="[747,828,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1858,1883]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,191,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,181,1839]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. S. shiqianensis Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. 2S abdominal apodemes; c. connective; d,i. anal tube appendage; e. apex of style, lateral view; f. style, dorsal view; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3933632/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
). Style slim and long, apical part extremely elongated, curved laterad, basal part short, slightly produced on inner margin subapically (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1177,549,576]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1858,1883]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,191,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,181,1839]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. S. shiqianensis Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. 2S abdominal apodemes; c. connective; d,i. anal tube appendage; e. apex of style, lateral view; f. style, dorsal view; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3933632/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Figs. 3e, f</figureCitation>
). Connective with manubrium long but narrow, compressed apophysis at apex of central lobe (
<figureCitation box="[966,1047,585,611]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1858,1883]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,191,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,181,1839]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. S. shiqianensis Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. 2S abdominal apodemes; c. connective; d,i. anal tube appendage; e. apex of style, lateral view; f. style, dorsal view; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3933632/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Fig. 3c</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft tubular, short and broad, without process, apex expanded with dorsal margin slightly convex in caudal view; pre-atrial process slim, broadened basally and slightly expanded subapically, remaining part uniform in thickness, curved dorsad basally and recurved ventrad apically in lateral view, apex reaching gonopore, gonopore subapical; dorsal apodeme moderately developed, obviously broader than aedeagal shaft and forked in caudal view (
<figureCitation box="[1079,1202,729,756]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1858,1883]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,191,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,181,1839]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. S. shiqianensis Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. 2S abdominal apodemes; c. connective; d,i. anal tube appendage; e. apex of style, lateral view; f. style, dorsal view; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3933632/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">
Figs. 
<quantity box="[1143,1173,729,755]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="371" unit="g" value="3.0">3g</quantity>
, h
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,261,1044]" box="[199,1166,765,792]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,371,766,792]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Measurement.</emphasis>
Length of male 
<quantity box="[556,714,765,791]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="371" unit="mm" value="3.65" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="3.6">3.60–3.70mm</quantity>
, female 4.00– 
<quantity box="[872,964,765,792]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.15" pageId="6" pageNumber="371" unit="mm" value="4.15">4.15mm</quantity>
(including wing).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
