<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="371" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,261,1044]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,910,936]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yang &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2014" box="[673,845,909,936]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Singapora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="371" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiantrosa">
<emphasis box="[673,845,909,936]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">S. longiantrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the apical patch on the vertex present in both male and female, style with apex gradually rather than sharply curved laterad, anal tube appendage with a tooth at the apex and dorsal apodeme obviously broader than the aedeagal shaft in caudal view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,984,1017,1044]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,261,1044]" box="[199,984,1017,1044]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1018,1044]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Etymology.</emphasis>
This new species is named for its 
<typeStatus box="[719,767,1018,1044]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">type</typeStatus>
locality “Shiqian”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
